The paper focuses on motion planning for automated vehicles, which is a core component of robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a learning-based approach using imitation learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of optimization techniques such as Mixed Integer Quadratic Problem (MIQP) suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach using experiments, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves analyzing visual data from the vehicle's sensors.
